# Accessibility UI Rules

For all interactive UI:

- All controls must have accessible labels.
- Keyboard-only users must be able to complete core flows.
- Focus state must be visible and not removed without replacement.
- Modal/dialog must trap focus and restore it on close.

## Semantics

- Use correct semantic roles for buttons, links, inputs, and dialogs.
- Avoid click-only divs when a button element is correct.
- Add ARIA attributes only when native semantics are insufficient.

## Error and status messaging

- Validation errors should be programmatically associated with fields.
- Important status changes should be announced accessibly.
